Creational Design Pattern
1. Singleton DP =>  Restricts instantiation to a single instance
2. Builder DP => if class has too many attributes, then it should create object with different attributes by using builder inner class to build object, Separates the construction of complex objects from their representation (e.g., User object creation).
3. Prototype & Registery DP => Prototype to make clone and register acts central cache to managed different type of this cloned objects
4. Factory DP => create object while using abstract factory to avoid dependency of one class in other class.Defines an interface for creating objects, letting subclasses determine the class to instantiate

Structural Design Pattern
1. Adapter DP => acts as adapter between two components
2. Facade DP => divide the responsibility of class,if that class hold too much responsibility
3. Decorator DP => Decorator design pattern allows us to dynamically add functionality and behavior to an object without affecting the behavior of other existing objects within the same class.
4. FlyWeight DP => If object is taking more memory than u can store intrinsic(value is same everytime) and extrinsic(value changes everytime) properties
    separately.

Behaviourly Design Pattern
1. Strategy DP => whenever we have mutiple ways to do something use strategy DP example : GOogle find path, Encapsulates interchangeable algorithms, allowing behavior selection at runtime
2. Observer DP => Whenever there is to notify other component use Observer DP example: Notification,Subscribtion, Defines a one-to-many dependency, notifying dependents of state changes
3. Command DP => Command DP encapsulate request as an Object,allowing to paramatrized Client with differnt request,or queue request or support undoable operations.